### Grid Gap

The `gap` or gutter between grid items makes use of the `spacing` design tokens which use an incremental scale to determine the size computed in the browser in `rem`s.
This is where a value of `100` is equal to `.25rem`.

| value | size (in `rem`) |
|-----------|-----------------|
| 100 | .25rem |
| 200 | .5rem |
| 400 | 1rem |
| 500 | 1.25rem |
| 600 | 1.5rem |
| 800 | 2rem |
| 1200 | 3rem |
